---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('mass');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Definition</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">Density, not volume.</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Mass</strong> is the substance and depth that builds around the Identity Stem. It is not surface area or activity level — it is owned stake with weight, history, and resistance to casual displacement.
				</p>
				<p>
					In the framework, Mass carries a central role in relation to tension: it provides the **inner Festigkeit** (cohesive strength) that allows an identity to bear, absorb, and productively use the multidimensional tension it encounters and generates.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Mass and Tension</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55 mb-6">
					Every identity exists within and generates a high-dimensional tension field. Mass is the primary resource that determines how much of this tension an identity can actually carry without fragmenting or collapsing.
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-5 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension-bearing capacity:</strong> Higher Mass increases the identity’s ability to hold conflicting demands, emotional load, external pressure, and self-generated tension (e.g. from strong Rotation) without losing coherence.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Absorption of centrifugal tension:</strong> Strong Rotation generates its own outward/expansion pressure (Fliehkraft-ähnlich). Without sufficient Mass, this self-generated tension becomes fragmenting rather than expansive.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Feedback into the field:</strong> Creating Mass changes the curvature around the identity. This altered curvature then acts back as new tension. Mass creation is therefore one of the most direct ways an identity can consciously shape its own tension field.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Engineering</div>
				<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl font-bold text-white md:text-4xl">What we work on</h2>
				<ul class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Owned stake:</strong> depth we can defend without performance. What would still pull if applause vanished?
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Density over spread:</strong> fewer domains with real weight beat many thin affiliations.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Conversion:</strong> convert rest mass into agency by moving coherently along the stem (State Differential and Vision Gradient aligned).
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension capacity:</strong> deliberately build Mass in areas where you want to sustainably hold more productive tension (e.g. long-term projects, deep relationships, complex responsibilities).
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6">
					<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/40 mb-3">Quick self-check</div>
					<ul class="space-y-3 text-white/60 leading-relaxed">
						<li>Where do I currently have high activity but low owned stake (low tension-bearing capacity)?</li>
						<li>What remains if external validation disappears for 90 days?</li>
						<li>Which commitment would meaningfully increase my ability to hold important tension?</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<p>
					Mass alone does not define identity. It gives the stem the substance and cohesion required to exist inside — and actively shape — a high-dimensional tension field. Without sufficient Mass, even coherent Rotation and clear Vision eventually collapse under the tension they themselves help generate.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="mass" />
	</main>
</Layout>
